Let $p(x) = x^n + a_1 x^{n-1} + \cdots + a_n \in \mathbb{C}[x]$ be a monic polynomial. Its
**companion matrix** $C \in \mathbb{C}^{n \times n}$ is

$$C = \begin{pmatrix}
0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & -a_n \\
1 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & -a_{n-1} \\
0 & 1 & \cdots & 0 & -a_{n-2} \\
\vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots & \vdots \\
0 & 0 & \cdots & 1 & -a_1
\end{pmatrix}.$$

Let $A \in \mathbb{C}^{m \times m}$ be an arbitrary matrix with eigenvalues $\lambda_1, \ldots, \lambda_m$
(counted with multiplicity). Define the block matrix

$$M = C \otimes I_m \;-\; I_n \otimes A \;\in\; \mathbb{C}^{mn \times mn},$$

where $\otimes$ denotes the Kronecker product and $I_k$ is the $k \times k$ identity matrix.

```figure caption="Structure of the block matrix $M$ for $n=3$, $m=2$. Each block is $2 \times 2$."
# A grid of 3Ă—3 blocks, each 2Ă—2. Show the companion structure.

# Frame for the 6Ă—6 block structure
path d="M(0,0) L(6,0) L(6,6) L(0,6) Z" fill=none stroke=black width=0.5

# Block grid lines
path d="M(2,0) L(2,6)" stroke=gray style=dashed width=0.3
